  "prompt": "Do US presidents get bodyguard protection after they have left the office?",
  "response": "Yes, former U.S. presidents and their spouses are entitled to Secret Service protection for the rest of their lives, as provided by the **Former Presidents Protection Act of 2012**. This law ensures that former presidents receive lifelong protection from the U.S. Secret Service. However, their children receive protection only until they turn 16.\n\nThere was a brief period between 1994 and 2013 when the law limited Secret Service protection to 10 years after leaving office. However, this was reversed in 2012 after concerns about the safety of former presidents. \n\nIn addition to security, former presidents receive other benefits, such as a pension, office space, staff assistance, and travel expenses, as outlined by the **Former Presidents Act of 1958**.",
